IMG2PDF – CURRENT AVAILABLE ARGUMENTS
======================================

REQUIRED ARGUMENTS
------------------
-command=img2pdf
    Must be exactly "img2pdf"

-input=PATH
    Folder containing images

-output=FILE.pdf
    Output PDF file path


OPTIONAL ARGUMENTS
==================

-pageSize=VALUE
---------------
Controls page sizing mode.

Supported values:
    A5, A4, A3, A2, A1, A0, 2A0
        → Force all pages to that ISO size (portrait)

    1_1
        → Page size = image physical size + margin

    auto
        → Snap to ISO paper if within threshold

    (not provided)
        → Default = image physical size


-percentThreshold=NUMBER
------------------------
Used only with:
    -pageSize=auto

Default: 5

If image physical size differs from ISO paper by less than this percentage,
that ISO size will be used.


-fitWidth=MM
------------
Example:
    -fitWidth=250

Meaning:
    Page width = 250 mm (portrait width)
    Page height = proportional to image
    Margin works
    Stretch works
    Ignores pageSize
    Ignores auto mode

NOTE:
    This is the highest priority layout mode.


-margin=MM
----------
Default: 8

Controls margin on all sides.

Works in all modes.
In 1_1 mode, page expands to include margin.


-stretch=y
----------
If set:
    Image is stretched to fill available margin rectangle.

If not set:
    Image is scaled proportionally.

Disabled automatically when:
    -pageSize=1_1


-numberOffset=MM
----------------
Default: 4

Distance from bottom-left corner for page number.


PAGE SIZE PRIORITY ORDER
=========================
Highest → Lowest

1) -fitWidth
2) -pageSize=1_1
3) -pageSize=A4 (or other ISO)
4) -pageSize=auto
5) Default → image physical size


FULL ARGUMENT SUMMARY
=====================

-command=img2pdf
-input=PATH
-output=FILE.pdf
-pageSize=A4|A3|A2|A1|A0|2A0|1_1|auto
-fitWidth=MM
-percentThreshold=NUMBER
-margin=MM
-stretch=y
-numberOffset=MM